ader.miniflux.app/proxy/_BbqDyxLgNpTcJavC- 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/j1CbsjbbEkw5vchmU-nRuxQKxupL4li-XCBiDfNDTjI=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY1MTAzNGRlYS1jMGM0LTQ4ZWQtYTZhMy0zNzRmNDMwM2YyOTZfMTkyMHgxMDgwLmpwZWc= 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/tGd2Lx6Cdt2Jv4LYwn6z7q5rr00eaTrEolXn4IW-jNA=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGNTEwMzRkZWEtYzBjNC00OGVkLWE2YTMtMzc0ZjQzMDNmMjk2XzE5MjB4MTA4MC5qcGVn 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/13bE9selu2d- 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/EfR-" width="728" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux. 424w, https://reader.miniflux. 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/lxFjE13Qy9_7eDGY7HcRVQ7ACSOCEHzHKjOEE3-plwc=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGNTEwMzRkZWEtYzBjNC00OGVkLWE2YTMtMzc0ZjQzMDNmMjk2XzE5MjB4MTA4MC5qcGVn 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/EfR- 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a><figcaption>1930-11</figcaption></figure><p>But it wasn’t all graphic hokum. Some ads, like the cartogram below, presented graphics that would still be considered sophisticated.</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6313ad7b-c969-4260-9744-36998c961a76_1920x1920.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Ka-h835xOJ7_fM7bgPpZbqjaSIAkQqw22I_8SRY3UQQ=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY2MzEzYWQ3Yi1jOTY5LTQyNjAtOTc0NC0zNjk5OGM5NjFhNzZfMTkyMHgxOTIwLmpwZWc= 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/hPPtYOuyXJ6j0f4AoMKhQ51seLvRobDpVtd2grS-fWg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY2MzEzYWQ3Yi1jOTY5LTQyNjAtOTc0NC0zNjk5OGM5NjFhNzZfMTkyMHgxOTIwLmpwZWc= 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/xhHGMJtdJSc6Q2GVWPbFaq5wTy-ckRc9lRzZP2Hx_8c=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGNjMxM2FkN2ItYzk2OS00MjYwLTk3NDQtMzY5OThjOTYxYTc2XzE5MjB4MTkyMC5qcGVn 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/vHxU8PaHsnTOkDIlPRWzULIp_ 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/29FLhZDCWYhOHhOZuKkM0ly--" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/14553Vi9wN24qRcgW159WIii_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/AHr50UoSQlVox_r0fnRgM6PS_ 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/29FLhZDCWYhOHhOZuKkM0ly-- 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a><figcaption>1929-05</figcaption></figure><p>This wasn’t the only data-sized cartogram I found. Another sized states by their farm market, emphasizing the Upper Mississippi Valley. Cartograms were all the rage in the 1920s, championed by patent-holder Karl G. Karsten, who wrote:</p><blockquote><p>We do not sell our goods to the mountains, bill them to the rivers, or credit the forests with payment. Probably from at least a subconscious appreciation of this circumstance, many national distributors, advertisers, and sales-managers have discarded maps on which the rivers, forests or mountains are shown when they are studying the geographic distribution of their sales. . . . Your sales manager does not sell to square miles, acres, or other units of land-area measurement. He sells to human beings. Why should he use maps which show, not human beings, but square miles, that is, maps in which the areas indicate not the population but the land surface? Why indeed!</p><p><em>Charts and Graphs</em> (1925), <a href="https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.223559/page/n673/mode/2up" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">p. 623</a>.</p></blockquote><p>The fancy charts are fun, but there were plenty of simple and tiny charts too.</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F60aa2cde-5237-41d6-9c01-dd079692bc70_2160x3840.png" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/pwUTMbAsE42VrxTulPyNzNjmDT1RnE23mO_BACbCi9Q=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY2MGFhMmNkZS01MjM3LTQxZDYtOWMwMS1kZDA3OTY5MmJjNzBfMjE2MHgzODQwLnBuZw== 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ZH2_9DKl_mhnNZzI6Mn5D- 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/jpocp7zpv3go3In6fkmsw58mIuIf_ 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux." alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux. 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/YsMK9wEF3sv- 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/AgqEn3F1PXRXpTQVzbEbm_ 1272w, https://reader.miniflux. 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p></p><p>A few had happy upward curves. Some had heroes.  Lots had <a href="https://www.datarevelations.com/bans/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">B.A.N.s</a>. </p><p>There are so many more—I pulled over a hundred information graphics! (Unfortunately we didn’t get to all of the maps, the best maps are ads for FORTUNE magazine and General Motors.) Many of these information graphics would pass today, indistinguishable from what modern organizations publish, nearly one hundred years later.</p><h2>What’s next</h2><p>If you know all about these charts, and especially who designed them and how they were created, I’d love to learn more.</p><p>Going forward, I&#39;m contemplating a deeper foray into TIME’s treasure chest. The next decade of exploration would encompass World War II, and promises even more chart riches. I welcome your thoughts on where my archival excavations should take me next.</p><p>While assembling these newsletters brings me immense joy, each edition demands substantial effort—often consuming several days. Please consider becoming a paid subscriber so the fun can keep rolling.</p><p><em>Onward!—RJ</em></p><p><em>Chartography</em> is supported by readers like you. Become a paid subscriber today.</p><h1>About</h1><p>Data storyteller RJ Andrews helps organizations solve high-stakes problems by using visual metaphors and information graphics: charts, diagrams, and maps. His passion is studying the history of information graphics to discover design insights. See more at <a href="http://infowetrust.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">infoWeTrust.com</a>.</p><p>RJ’s recently published series, <a href="https://visionarypress.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Information Graphic Visionaries</a>, a new book series celebrating three spectacular data visualization creators. With new writing, complete visual catalogs, and discoveries never seen by the public. His first book <em>Info We Trust, How to Inspire the World with Data</em>—will be published in a remastered edition in 2024.</p>